@startuml tmu_access_to_dkey_state_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title TMU Access To DKEY State Signal Flow\n(TMU service / signal bars / drive state -> DKEY access publication)

actor "Remote/User input\nTMU service request" as User #F4F7FB
participant "TMU / Vehicle input\nservice mode + signal bars + drive" as Inp #E8F0FE
participant "DKEY\ndigital key owner" as DKEY #E8F7E8
participant "Door / SMK / PAK\naccess consumers" as Access #FFF4CC
participant "TEST_SCN / observers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Access Inputs ==

User -> Inp : service request / radio proximity update
Inp -> DKEY : tmuServiceMode\nsignalBars\ndriveState
activate DKEY
DKEY -> DKEY : normalize stale TMU / vehicle inputs
DKEY -> DKEY : derive DKeyState / AuthMode
DKEY -> DKEY : derive VehicleAccessState / SecurityGrade
DKEY -> DKEY : update KeySyncAge / KeyPresence
note right of DKEY
Representative inputs
- tmuServiceMode
- signalBars
- driveState

Representative internal outputs
- DKeyState
- AuthMode
- VehicleAccessState
- SecurityGrade
- KeyPresence
- KeySyncAge
end note

== Access Publish ==

DKEY -> Access : frmDkeyStateMsg
DKEY -> Obs : traceable DKEY state for\nscenario/test observation
note right of Access
Representative consumers
- DOOR_FL / DOOR_FR / DOOR_RL / DOOR_RR
- SMK
- PAK
end note
deactivate DKEY

note over User, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. TMU service state and signal bars arrive with vehicle drive state
2. DKEY derives access/auth/security state and sync age
3. DKEY publishes frmDkeyStateMsg to door and key-related ECUs
4. Test and observer paths can confirm access-state transitions
end note

@enduml
